<TITLE> Janajuddho cadre killed in gunfight with police </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bagerhat, Dec 8 (bdnews24.com)Sheikh Murad, a leader of the outlawed Purbo Banglar Communist Party (Janajuddho), was kelled in a gunfight with police early on Tuesday at Fakirhat of the district. The 32-year-old communist cadre was earlier sentenced to death by a court in connection with a murder case involving the death in 2001 of SM Farhad Hossain, a local Awami League leader and an industrialist. The gun battle took place at around 4am Tuesday in a mahogany plantation near Shubhash Mallick's house in Brahmanrakdia village under Fakirhat Upazila. Murad's body was sent to Bagerhat sadar hospital for autopsy. Police recovered two shutter guns, five rounds of 303 rifle bullets, 16 rounds of live ammunition and seven empty ammunition cases from the scene. Fakirhat police chief Salahuddin Miah said that they were tipped off that Muradwho had been on the run for a long timereturned to his area and was holding a meeting with his militant cohorts in the village plantation. Police raided the village to nab Murad when a gun-fight ensued. They claimed Murad was injured in the gun-fight and later died after being taken to local health complex. Murad, son of Sheikh Lehazuddin of Baliadanga village, faced eight murder, extortion and robbery cases filed against him, police said. bdn
